question: Which two genes are predominantly considered by warfarin initial dosing algorithms?
ideal_answer: Polymorphisms in CYP2C9 and VKORC1 are taken into consideration by warfarin initial dosing algorithms.

snippets.text: 507 adults were randomized to receive initial dosing as determined by an algorithm containing genetic (VKORC1 and CYP2C9) plus clinical information or only clinical information.
